			"text": "Statistical language modeling ( LM ) ",
			"relation": "bg-goal"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "that purports to quantify the acceptability of a given piece of text ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "has long been an interesting yet challenging research area . <S>",
			"relation": "same-unit"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "In particular , language modeling for information retrieval ( IR ) has enjoyed remarkable empirical success ; ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "one emerging stream of the LM approach for IR is to employ the pseudo-relevance feedback process ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "to enhance the representation of an input query ",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "so as to improve retrieval effectiveness . <S>",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "This paper presents a continuation of such a general line of research ",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "and the main contribution is threefold . <S>",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "First , we propose a principled framework ",
			"relation": "elab-process_step"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "which can unify the relationships among several widely-used query modeling formulations . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "Second , on top of the successfully developed framework , we propose an extended query modeling formulation ",
			"relation": "elab-process_step"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "by incorporating critical query-specific information cues ",
			"relation": "manner-means"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "to guide the model estimation . <S>",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "Third , we further adopt and formalize such a framework to the speech recognition and summarization tasks . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-process_step"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "A series of empirical experiments reveal the feasibility of such an LM framework and the performance merits of the deduced models on these two tasks . <S>",
			"relation": "evaluation"
